subSubSection.paragraph:
Diagnosis of female.
Mandible with five sharpened apical teeth, two lower wider than others. Clypeus with median lobe trapezoidal with apical margin truncate (
Fig. 10
). Propodeal disc with five carinae, median and inner discal carinae complete, second pair of discal carina incomplete, with longitudinal ridge between median and inner discal carinae, with longitudinal ridge between inner discal carina and second pair of discal carina (
Fig. 11
). Propodeal declivity with median carina. Stigma with one short and thick dorsal setae. Radial vein straight and 0.8x basal vein (
Fig. 13
).

Mesosoma.
Pronotal disc coriaceous, trapezoidal, side slightly concave, punctures sparse, dorsal setae long and thick. Mesoscutum coriaceous, with long and thick setae between notaulus and parapsidal furrow. Notaulus conspicuous, incomplete, parallel. Parapsidal furrow shorter than notaulus, as conspicuous as notaulus, not reaching anterior margin of mesoscutum, parallel to each other. Scutellum coriaceous, with four pairs of thick setae. Propodeal disc 1.0x as long as wide, with five carinae; median carina complete; inner discal carinae complete; space between median and inner discal carinae with longitudinal ridge; second pair of discal carina incomplete; space between inner discal carina and second pair of discal carina with longitudinal ridge; sublateral carina absent; lateral carina present, followed by short striae; posterior carina complete (
Fig. 11
). Declivity of propodeum strigulate, median carina present. Mesopleuron with subtegular fovea; sub-alar fovea elongate and closed; anterior fovea opened; mesopleural fovea opened; lower fovea closed; posterior fovea closed; episternal furrow with inner margin not striate (
Fig. 12
).

Diagnosis of male.
Mandible with five sharpened apical teeth, two lower wider than others; with only one thick dorsal setae. Clypeus with median lobe trapezoidal with apical margin truncate (
Fig. 15
). Notaulus inconspicuous and straight. Parapsidal furrow shorter and narrower than notaulus. Propodeal disc with five carinae, median carina, inner discal carina and second pair of discal carina incomplete (
Fig. 16
). Propodeal declivity with median carina. Radial vein 1.22x longer than basal vein (
Fig. 20
).

Mesosoma.
Pronotal disc coriaceous, trapezoidal, side slightly concave, punctures sparse, dorsal setae long and thick. Mesoscutum coriaceous, with short and thick setae between notaulus and parapsidal furrow. Notaulus inconspicuous, incomplete, parallel. Parapsidal furrow shorter than notaulus, more conspicuous than notaulus, not reaching anterior margin of mesoscutum, parallel each other. Scutellum coriaceous, with four pairs of thick setae. Propodeal disc 1.13x as long as wide, with five carinae; median carina complete; inner discal carinae complete; space between median and inner discal carinae with ridge; second pair of discal carina complete; space between inner discal carina and second pair of discal carina with ridge; sublateral carina absent; lateral carina present, followed by short striae; posterior carina complete (
Fig. 16
). Declivity of propodeum strigulate, median carina present. Mesopleuron with subtegular fovea; sub-alar fovea elongate and closed; anterior fovea closed; mesopleural fovea opened; lower fovea opened; posterior fovea opened; episternal furrow with inner margin striate (
Fig. 18
).
